 meals to keep a diet of emergency food storage interesting.","You can buy items a la carte if you&#39;re looking to buy bulk buckets of meat or fruits and vegetables for long-term food storage, or you can go with kits that contain multiple types of food and a total of 90, 180 or 360 servings. The kits are nice because they take into account the whole meal. Even in an emergency it can be nice to have both an entree and dessert. Survival is most important but having foods that are familiar can be a great comfort.","Lindon Farms organizes sets of buckets that make it easy to buy what you need. There are three-month collections of food for one person, for example, that you can purchase as a group. You can also set up a subscription that allows you to build your total food storage over time. You pay a monthly fee and get a monthly shipment. If you store these cartons in a cool, dry location, much of the food stays good for up to 20 years.","This service does not lack for food and nutrition options, but its water sanitation choices are where it falls behind most of its competition. For a company that gives a complete diet plan, we are disappointed in Lindon Farms&#39; lack of options for water purification. The company doesn&#39;t provide fresh water boxes, water filters, desalination tablets or a stove. Without clean water, a surplus of survival food may not do you much good. You could, of course, buy the water purification and storage equipment separately but we prefer the food storage companies that offer one-stop shopping.","As people become more concerned with their health and what they allow themselves to eat, there is a strong focus on vegetarian and gluten-free options. This even applies to food storage. Lindon Farms does not currently provide either gluten-free or vegetarian meals. We appreciate that this dried food storage service provides free shipping, though. This is a big deal if you&#39;re ordering enough food to last you and your family for an entire year. <a href=\"/augason-farms-review\">Augason Farms</a> is a service with a large selection of vegetarian and gluten-free options."]},"id":"970947cf-3722-474d-a89a-4121f95c3585","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"90315c50-762e-4950-8fea-20c8d0ec9786","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Lindon Farms has a good variety of nutritious food options, and the convenience of free shipping and logical package deals make this an attractive option for long-term food storage. It also packages a variety of courses to give you the best possible assortment of good food. The company could have ranked higher if it also provided essential water sanitation tools and a few more options for specific dietary needs like gluten-free and vegetarian."]},"id":"52c520ee-b2ac-491f-8041-7ca3e80dd1a3","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_57027","url":"/lindon-farms-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"angie-parkinson","url":"/author/angie-parkinson","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Angie Parkinson","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"4Pu3Dbh8P3CR8CNSJRVPZP","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2013-07-16T14:26:48Z","datePublished":"2013-07-16T14:26:48Z","name":"Lindon Farms","synopsis":"Lindon Farms is a decent competitor when it comes to survival food storage options. The company's goals are clearly outlined on its website. It has equipment to help homes be prepared for disasters and offers enough food for a typical diet with all the basic food groups.","review":{"rating":46,"verdict":"Lindon Farms is missing water sanitation and storage equipment, but its buying options are convenient and the food options are many.","pros":["The package deals are nutritious and include different courses like drinks and desserts in addition to entrees."],"cons":["There are no specific gluten-free or peanut-free options for those with dietary restrictions."]},"strapline":"Lindon Farms is 